Senate Bill 343
By: Senators Hatchett of the 50th, Strickland of the 42nd and Tillery of the 19th
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Code Section 39-6-2 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to age
2 verification of account holders, minors, and information relating to available content
3 censorship or moderation features, so as to prohibit providers of social media platforms from
4 permitting a minor aged 14 years or younger to be an account holder; to provide for an
5 effective date; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other
6 purposes.
7 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
8 SECTION 1.
9 Code Section 39-6-2 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to age verification
10 of account holders, minors, and information relating to available content censorship or
11 moderation features, is amended by revising subsection (c) as follows:
12 "(c) No provider of a social media platform shall permit a minor aged 14 years or younger
13 to be an account holder. No provider of a social media platform shall permit a minor older
14 than 14 years of age to be an account holder unless such provider obtains the express
15 consent of such minor's parent or guardian. Acceptable methods of obtaining express
16 consent from a parent or guardian include:
