17 (1) Providing a form for the minor's parent or guardian to sign and return to the social
18 media platform by common carrier, facsimile, email, or scanning;
19 (2) Providing a toll-free telephone number for the minor's parent or guardian to call to
20 consent;
21 (3) Coordinating a call with the minor's parent or guardian using videoconferencing
22 technology;
23 (4) Collecting information related to the minor's parent's or guardian's government issued
24 identification or financial or payment card information and deleting such information
25 after confirming the identity of the parent or guardian;
26 (5) Allowing the minor's parent or guardian to provide consent by responding to an email
27 and taking additional steps to verify the parent's or guardian's identity; and
28 (6) Any other commercially reasonable method of obtaining consent using available
29 technology."
30 SECTION 2.
31 This Act shall become effective on July 1, 2025.
32 SECTION 3.
33 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
